resources.title: Investing in Health Community Change
resources.description: Active Living by Design (ABLD) is an organization that created community-led change by working with partners at all levels of government to build a culture of active living and healthy eating. This report focuses on way to enhance the relationship between funders and the communities funded. When both sides leverage their resources, they are better able to achieve their goals and sustain their results. It does this by highlighting the successes and challenges of such partnerships across the country in a series of case studies.

resources.title: Lessons for Leaders
resources.description: Active Living by Design (ABLD) is an organization that created community-led change by working with partners at all levels of government to build a culture of active living and healthy eating. This report focuses on some of the challenges leaders might face when implementing ambitious, long-term projects to improve the health of a community. The report’s core lessons emerged from experience in creating change. They are broadly applicable and stimulate reflection that can help improve the quality of decisions.

resources.title: AHRQ Health Care Innovations Exchange
resources.description: The Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ) created the Health Care Interventions Exchange to speed the implementation of new and better ways of delivering healthcare. The exchange supports AHRQ’s mission to produce evidence to make health care safer, of higher quality, more accessible, equitable, and affordable. The Innovations Exchange also allows health professionals and researchers share, learn about, and adopt evidence-based innovations and tools for a variety of healthcare settings and populations.

resources.title: Assessing the Value of Investments in Primary Prevention
resources.description: The Altarum Institute Center for Sustainable Health Spending, with funding from the Robert Wood Johnson Foundation, is creating a model to demonstration how interventions outside of the medical system can impact healthcare costs. This report gives a brief overview of how this tool can be used to describe the financial and health impacts of investments in prevention. The tool is meant to capture as many expected benefits and costs as possible.

resources.title: Asset-Based Community Development Toolkit (ABCD) Toolkit
resources.description: The Asset-Based Community Development Institute is an organization dedicated to community building work. It specifically focuses on community capacity, community-based participatory research, working directly with communities, and producing publications and resources for others. Their toolkit offers guidance on communicating the principles of ABCD, discovering assets available to communities, and ways to facilitate collaboration.

resources.title: Association for Community Health Improvement
resources.description: The Association for Community Health Improvement (ACHI) is an association for community health, community benefit, and healthy community professionals. Their website offers education, professional development, networking, and practical tools that help leaders expand their knowledge and enhance their performance in achieving community health goals.

resources.title: Primary Care and Public Health Integration
resources.description: ASTHO is a nonprofit organization that represents the 100,000 public health professionals across the US, its territories, and DC. Its members ensure sound public health policy and excellence in state-based public health practice. ASTHO created a website that offers resources on ways to integrate primary care and public health. It has features a strategic map, success stories, webinars, and other resources that can help people interested in improving population health identify strategies and challenges that might assist them in their goal.
